<TITLE> Two committees to investigate death in custody </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Comilla, July 3 (bdnews24.com)  Two committees were formed Tuesday to investigate the death of Munshi Munsur Ali while in hospital under police remand. Ali was arrested in Comilla on June 24 for making illegal-toll demands. Police took him to hospital on July 2 where he died within 15 minutes of arrival. The committees, formed by the district administration and the police administration in Comilla, have three members each. They will submit their findings within three days. bd
